The paper deals with two-player, turn-based, stochastic games with reachability conditions, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of deterministic and mixed strategies, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of deciding maxmin reachability involves analyzing the game structure and finding optimal strategies, which can be approached using techniques from discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.LO). Finally, the paper deals with the concept of perfect information and memory requirements, which are relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
